translated: HuIIing, Einar Olof, High School Teacher, Varberg, born on July 16th, 1891 in Norrköping to estate owner Albert H. and Elin Olofsson. He passed his high school exams in Norrköping in 1910, graduated with a Bachelor of Philosophy from Uppsala University in 1913 and received his Master of Philosophy from Lund University in 1915. He verified his education in 1915 and again in 1928, did a trial year at Gothenburg's upper secondary school in Latin from 1920 to 1921. He was a vicar in Kristinehamn in 1918, a substitute teacher in Karliskoga from 1918 to 1919, a vicar in Mariestad from 1919 to 1920, and a full-time teacher and vicar in Växjö from 1921 to 1922. He was a vicar in Västervik in 1923, a vicar and adjunct teacher at the School of the People in Linköping from 1923 to 1925, a full-time teacher in Linköping from 1925 to 1926, a substitute teacher at Malmö Secondary School in 1927, at the new Oak School in Stockholm from 1928 to 1930, and in Halmstad from 1930 to 1931. He was a full-time adjunct teacher in Norrköping from 1931 to 1932, a teacher in Arvika from 1932 to 1934, and a teacher of mother tongue, history, social science, and geography at Varberg's social people school since 1934.
